text: Lauren May Hemp (born 7 August 2000), is a professional football player from England. She plays as a forward for Manchester City in the Women's Super League and also represents the England national team. She received the England Young Player of the Year award in September 2016 and 2017, and she was named the PFA Women's Young Player of the Year in 2018, 2019, 2020, and 2022. == References == Category:English footballers Category:Female footballers Category:2000 births Category:Living people
